name: Big bedroom in friendly flat share in Camberwell
summary: I'm away for 3 weeks this September so would like to let my large, comfortable lower ground floor bedroom with en-suite out for the duration. The bathroom has shower and bath, and my bed has a memory foam mattress topper -best purchase of my life! Sheets and towels incl. The flat is on the ground floor of an art deco building in the arty, relaxed area of Camberwell, with the best little park in London just round the corner. It is well equipped and my flat mates are lovely, interesting  people.
space: Large bedroom with a double bed, desk, clothes rail, and chest of drawers. Ensuite bathroom with bath, shower, sink and toilet. Would suit someone staying in London for a few weeks for work or to explore. Has a rather interesting glass brick wall instead of a window, which is the only downside, but upstairs is very light and airy with high ceilings and big windows, which makes up for the slightly odd design downstairs.

neighborhood_overview: Camberwell is a great area of London, green and calm but with lots of independent cafes and pubs. There is an established art college so it's a nice bohemian vibe in this historically Afro-Caribbean neighbourhood, without it being sickeningly hipster.
notes: We have three bathrooms and we're really proud of this fact, just wanted to let you know.
transit: Camberwell doesn't have a tube BUT  the bus links to Vauxhall/Oval/Elephant and Castle/ Anywhere are super sweet and the flat is a 15min walk from Denmark Hill Overground Station and Loughborough Junction real train station. A great base in south London for someone for a few weeks.
access: You'd have your own keys. The room is in a flatshare with three wonderful and friendly  housemates. The flat is on two floors - on the ground floor, there is a living room and two bedrooms. Next door is a kitchen, with all the typical kitchen amenities you would expect.
interaction: We'd welcome you into our home! You'd be treated exactly like a normal flatmate but excused the chores!  My flat mates are Chris (a boy) who is very glamourous, clever and works for a think tank, Octavia (a girl) who is also very glamourous and clever and is a copywriter and Sequoia (a girl) who is gorgeous and a very talented photographer. We're all in our 20s and between the three of them speak: French, German and Spanish. We're a very happy house, making each other laugh and dinner from time to time, but  we all have different jobs and keep different hours so you wouldn't be forced to socialise on a week night if you didn't want to.
house_rules: We basically would like people to have a nice time. We all like the house looking good and the kitchen being clean, but understand if someone is in a rush in the morning then their plate being out is not the end of the world. We regularly sit around the wobbly kitchen table and chat in the evenings, which is nice because we all have different jobs and friendship groups.
host_about: Friendly, out-going Brit who grew up in Germany.

neighborhood_overview: Beautiful Barnsbury is full of Georgian and Victorian properties along leafy, romantic streets. There is also selection of open spaces and garden squares in the area, almost all of which are open to the public.  The area features some of the most prestigious property in Islington, and some of the most beautiful streets, with Ripplevale Grove, Barnsbury Square and Lonsdale Square among the most sought-after addresses.  Traditional English pubs serving upscale gastro fare to well-heeled clients mix with some more cutting edge offerings closer to Upper Street, and it is this mix of the traditional English charm on the doorstep of the bustle and international flavours of Upper Street and Kings Cross which lend the area much of its appeal.
notes: We have a friendly and cuddly cat named Tiger who will need to be fed twice a day. Food will be left in the kitchen.
transit: Tube: You have access to the Highbury & Islington tube stop which is approx 10 minutes walk away on the Victoria line. Overground: There is an overground stop (Caledonian Road & Barnsbury) less than 5 minutes walk away. Bus: Access to numerous bus lines less than 5 minutes walk away on Hemingford Road and Caledonian Road.

neighborhood_overview: Dulwich  is a nice, green leafy and safe residential area, feels like countryside (especially Dulwich Village), but has got good tranport links to the central. The house is located in a quiet street. There are nice independent shops, restaurants, cafés, pubs, bakery, green grocery, butchery, laundry run by locals within 2-10 minutes of walk.  There is also a GP surgery, pharmacy, library, Tesco, Sainsbury,  Asda, Barclays, Lloyds  around the area. Dulwich Village is 20 mins walk with lovely shops, cafés, a bakery and  a great pub.  If you are sporty we have a nice gym in West Norwood, Brockwell Lido with open-air pool  is just 2 mins train ride or 20 mins walk and the nearby Dulwich College also offers sport facilities. We have got tennis and horse riding schools around as well. There are 2 lovely parks in 10 min's walk (Brockwell and Dulwich), and the bustling Brixton is just 5 mins train ride away.  Brixton is getting the new trendy area with its multitude of bars and restaurants wit
transit: We have got 3 train stations (West Dulwich, Tulse Hill, West Norwood) within 10-15 mins walk as well as great bus services and night services to and from Central London. London Bridge is 18 mins, Victoria is 12 mins train ride, Clapham Junction is 10 mins,  Blackfriars is 10  mins by train.  Nearest tube station is Brixton with 5 mins train ride. Brixton is on the Victoria line just 8 minutes from Victoria, 12 minutes from Oxford Circus and 20 minutes from Kings Cross.  If you come by car you will have free off street parking here always with available slot to park nearby the house.
access: You are welcome to use all the facilities provided. There is fast and unlimited wi-fi and cable TV - although at the moment there is no TV set. There is a  dishwasher, microwave, kettle, toaster, fridge, freezer and washing machine. You will be given kitchen cupboard space so that you can feel free to use the kitchen and cook your own meal. I have complimentary tea and coffee for those ones who stay for a week or less. Also breakfast is available on request.  I can provide adaptor, Oyster card and plenty of maps and tourist guides.   The upstairs living room is shared with me, I work part time at home from there but feel free to enjoy what it has to offer (books, DVDs, CDs) or just sit around.   There is a shed in the back garden where you can keep your bike if you have one.
interaction: I guess I live the average London life: busy with a hectic schedule. This is my home where I relax but I am available to help you settle. I can give you tips and hints about where to go, what to see, I can show you around locally.  If time and work permits I am happy to have some program together with you but a lot depends on your needs a well.
house_rules: This is a friendly and easygoing house shared only by me and my housemate (a nice female). We want you to have a great stay so we will provide you with a clean, tidy and welcoming house where you can feel home and are welcome to use all the facilities provided. In return you are expected to be a mature, considerate, reliable, tidy and clean person who respects us and our house.   No heavy smokers! No problem if you are an occasional smoker but you need to do that outside. Only guests known to me are allowed into the premises. Please note that, in line with Airbnb's terms and conditions of booking: you must conduct yourself in the manner of Responsible Guests and Invitees. You will be responsible for all Covered Losses.  You are obliged to pay for damages or losses for any Covered Property caused by yourselves.  If there is any problem, please feel free to discuss it with me.  Wishing you a pleasant stay!
host_about:
I run my own enterprise as interior stylist and colour consultant. 
Love travelling, walking barefoot, eating chocolate, reading and writing, screaming into the air from the edge of a cliff, surrounding myself great (and sometimes odd) things and people. What goes around comes around is my guiding principle. And I am greatful to have my two "mind laboratory advisers": Albert Einstein and Audrey Hepburn.
I did Couchirfing in the past, both hosting and being a guest and have been sharing spaces with others for years so I am comfortable with this and know what it takes to be a good host.

A lovely, warm, spacious family home with great links into the centre of town and the City as well as a stunning park and lots of amenities on the doorstep.  We have a well equipped, very light kitchen which looks out to our newly landscaped garden - complete with bi-folding doors. There is a combi-washing / drying machine and dishwasher. The dining area has a table that comfortably seats 6 but can be extended to have 10 (though we've squeezed in more!) Also on the ground floor is a double reception room with two comfortable sofas and a TV (with BT infinity package and DVD player) There is high speed wireless internet throughout the house.  Upstairs there are three bedrooms.  A huge master bedroom with Superking bed.  Lovely original sash windows and thick curtains.

neighborhood_overview: It is a fantastic neighbourhood.  Very family orientated but with excellent links to central London - for all things cultural plus shopping and every restaurant imaginable.  We love Brockwell Park (5 mins walk)  with great views of London as well as a brilliant playground - BMX track - tennis courts - pretty gardens - paddling pool as well as a truly glorious 50 meter Lido complete with fantastic cafe (delicious coffees and cakes as well as cocktails!) There are two gastropubs nearby and several lovely cafes - an award winning bakery and butchers and some lovely shops.  There's a farmer's market every Sunday. It is a 15 minute walk to leafy Dulwich village - very picturesque with an art gallery and superb grounds and cafe  - with two parks (Dulwich and Belair)
transit: V convenient public transport.  Herne Hill train station is a 6  min walk.  Direct lines to: London Victoria (9 mins), perfect for nipping up to Oxford Street or Blackfriars (11 mins) perfect for the world famous Southbank with The Tate Modern and general Thames life. We have a bus stop 30 seconds from our house which goes to Brixton and onto Oxford Street (via Picadilly Circus/Hamley's etc) So, we not only have several lovely gastro pubs, cafes and restaurants within a few minutes walk of our house, but also a v short journey to  Brixton with its fashionable and wonderful 'Brixton Village' full of eclectic cafes, bars and restaurants as well as excellent cinema.  If you wanted to bring a car - we can get you parking permits at an extra cost (around 5 pounds per day)

neighborhood_overview: Our apartment is situated just off Roman Road, right in the middle of Victoria Park, Bethnal Green, Hackney Wick and Bow. The nice and historical Roman Road market takes place three times a week just right outside our house. Brick Lane, Shoreditch, Columbia Road & Broadway Market - with a huge mix of galleries, shops, markets, bars, pubs and restaurants - are all very close to our place. You can also find many interesting local attractions in the neighbourhood including Lauriston Road Village - for its beautiful cafes, pubs and stores - and Columbia Road, Broadway Market and Dalston for their markets, restaurants and nightlife.
notes: Check in: flexible   Check out: 12 (noon)
transit: There are many buses and trains that you can use: Bethnal Green’s central line - which is one of the main and fastest line in London - is just 10 mins away, as well as Hackney Wick and Bow stations, where you can also take the District, Hammersmith & City line, DLR and overground. Buses and night buses to central London are frequent and only a 1 minute walk from the house. Examples of journey times from Bethnal Green station:  Oxford Circus = 20 mins by tube Liverpool Street = 3 mins by tube / 11 mins by bus / 25 mins walking Shoreditch High Street = 10 minutes by bus / 20 mins walking  Airports:  London City Airport - 15 mins by car Stanstead - 35 mins by car  Heathrow - 60 mins by car  Gatwick - 60 mins by car
access: Your room is just two steps from the bathroom that offers a combined bath and shower. Guests have use of hair, body and bath products. The kitchen if fully equipped and you are welcome to use it for some light cooking. There is a fibre fast connection throughout the house that you can enjoy. We’ve also got a NETFLIX and BT Sport account that you’re welcome to use. You also have the use of an iron, ironing board and washing machine.

Brockley is a diverse, friendly community with a thriving arts scene.  Fabulous restaurants cafes and bars nearby: The Gantry, The Orchard and Mo Pho, all near Brockley station are recommended and very close by. We also have lots of delicious Caribbean, Indian, Thai restaurants and take away, and the best chips in London at Brockley's Rock.

The park is massive and offers playground, dinosaurs (!), events, and great views.  The nearby Gipsy Hill train station takes you to London Bridge (20 mins) with the infamous Shard and great Borough market, and also takes you to central Victoria train station.

Or you could do what I do - cycle :) You can hire bikes outside the flat and it takes about 20 minutes to cycle into the centre, while Shoreditch, Brick Lane and Dalston are very close. The best thing about this flat is being in such a peaceful spot right next to the canal and Victoria Park, while being in the middle of an exciting area with great restaurants, bars and culture. Next to the apartment is a large park, while the magnificent Victoria Park is a 5-minute walk and the Regent's Canal is right outside the window. You can also easily walk to Broadway Market, Columbia Road and Roman Road market. Bank, cash machines, post office and grocery shops are all on your doorstep.
notes: There is a sofa in the living room which is good for sleeping on for a fifth person, if needed. However, it is not a sofa bed as such. Also, there are no curtains in the living room so it is bright in the mornings.

If you like walking, the canal takes you all the way to the Angel Islington about three miles away. I really recommend this walk.

neighborhood_overview: The neighborhood is a great mix of beautiful English houses and converted factory buildings which have made it attractive for all kinds of creatively driven people. A lot of the streets are cycling streets, so there are not that many cars around. If you have some time to just take a walk around the area, you will forget about the fact that you are in one of Europe's biggest capitals. Nevertheless the lively parts of Shoreditch with interesting restaurants, bars and stores are all in walking distance and easy to get to.  At the weekends you can get fresh flowers on Columbia Road or try the diverse food stands at broadway market, selling everything from bacon to beans. On lazy days you can just walk down the road to the canal, have a coffee at one of the lovely cafes and gaze on the water. Whatever you are looking for, you will definitely find it in this area. Spice Island does brilliant Indian take away! The Scolt’s Head / Talbot and De Beauvoir Arms are lovely local pubs The De Beauvoi
notes: We do rent out the space for shoots and events as well. Please discuss this with us before your booking!
transit: 76 bus via Old street (right in front of the door) Kingsland road is right around the corner with all sorts of bus routes ((PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)) to either Shoreditch or Hackney/Dalston The next Overground Station is Haggerston or Dalston Junction (5 minute walk). The next tube stations are Shoreditch Highstreet or Old Street.
access: To enter the apartment you will walk through a large garage door that is shared with the studio next door. The studio next door is used as a home and yoga space, studio for photos ect. So you may see people in and out of the garage and garden. Please note, that the garden is a communal space and you might not be alone all the time. It would be great if you could engage in watering the flowers from time to time in case we ask you to...
house_rules: Since the apartments are situated very close to each other and they are all on the ground floor, please understand that it is not a party place and we would like the neighbors to be treated respectfully...

host_about:
I was born an bred in Brazil, and have been living in London for just under 4 years now.

I absolutely love seeing the world. And even though, meeting new people and  cultures is my passion, I've made London my home, and am truly in love with this city.

London has everything you could ask for, being immersed in this soup of cultures is always inspiring and that's why London is always surprising me and reinventing myself and my ideas of the world. 
I have been all around this city and from traditional Kensington to hipstery Shoreditch, I can say London has something for everyone.

As much as I love travelling, I know how important it is to be in the perfect location and feel comfortable and safe, so you can only focus on going out and exploring new things. And, I'll do my very best to give you all you need to have an amazing time.

Welcome to London.

space: Our open plan kitchen and living area enjoys marvellous sunshine for most of the day, with dual aspect, ceiling to floor windows overlooking the river and nature reserve. In summer, cattle graze on the marsh but you are still very much in central London - a unique urban rural feel. The first bedroom  features a king size bed, and the second bedroom a double futon. Our flat sleeps 4 comfortably. The bathroom is very spacious, also with ceiling to floor windows and lots of natural light.

You will have access to our media centre, w
neighborhood_overview: Where we live is a very special place. Clapton is a rapidly up and coming area, with a range of unique bars and eateries and the gourmet Sunday food markets on Chatsworth Road nearby. Whether you want a great breakfast, to stay out partying, do a bit of boutique shopping, or have a serene walk in the nature reserve and admire the Galloway Band Cattle, it's all here.  Not many flats in Zone 2 have such easy access to acres of green space. I love running, and being right on the towpath next to the river means I can run for hours without ever crossing a road. Lea Valley Ice Rink and Riding Centre are just a short walk away. These facilities, with the sights, shopping, theatres and  museums of central London less than half an hour away make our neighbourhood pretty special. The exciting shopping and nightlife of Dalston and Shoreditch are just a short bus ride away, and the buses run all night! It is a truly unique London experience. I was born in Hackney and have travelled all over the wo
transit: The 393 bus which runs from Clapton Pond to Highbury and Islington Tube (Victoria Line) stops right outside the flat. Clapton Rail is ten mins walk away, and will take you into central London (Liverpool Street) in 12 mins. Dalston and Shoreditch can be easily reached on the 55, 56 or 48 buses, which are a ten min walk away. Route 253 and 254 are 7 mins walk away and will take you into central London, or for a quicker journey you can hop off and switch to the tube at Manor House (Piccadilly Line) or Bethnal Green (Central Line) after a 10 minute journey on the bus. From the airports, Stansted is less than an hour away, with the Stansted Express taking you to Liverpool Street in 47 mins, and the train from Liverpool Street to Clapton a 12 minute journey. By car, the journey takes 40 minutes. Heathrow is easily reachable via the Piccadilly Line from Manor House, driving will take about 90 minutes, depending on the time of day.
access: Guests will have access to the whole flat. We have a fully fitted kitchen with dishwasher and a washing machine. Hot water is on demand and central heating also, but the flat is well insulated and doesn't need it in summer. You will have access to our media centre, with an extensive video library and state of the art speakers - great for a night in watching films or listening to music.
interaction: Either ourselves or a member of my family will be there to greet you but we won't be around the flat during your stay. However, either us or a member of the family will be on hand in case you need us  - but only if you want us to be!
house_rules: We don't allow pets or smoking. We are fairly relaxed but will expect you to leave the flat as tidy as you found it. Feel free to have guests but please be mindful of our neighbours.
host_about: I am a classical guitarist who teaches and plays around the London area, details on my website (URL HIDDEN) I have lived with my partner Madalein in our home in Clapton, East London for 2 years. Madalein teaches English in a local secondary school.

neighborhood_overview: The apartment is situated in the heart of London's Stockwell/Brixton area, and will be an ideal home away from home for your trip to London, and the perfect vantage point from which to experience this vibrant, culture-drenched city. Nearby attractions include Brixton (for the academy venue, famous market, many restaurants and bars), and the River Thames. Green spaces like Clapham Common, Herne Hill are very close by, while Battersea Park and Kew Gardens are within easy reach by bus or train. Attractions like the Southbank (London eye/London Aquarium), Houses of Parliament, The London Dungeons, and the West End are also very easily accessible via tube or bus.
notes: Check-in time is usually after 3pm and check-out time is usually before 11am. If you would like to arrive or leave at a different time, please let us know and we will try our best to accommodate. Please note that you will be charged £100 for lost keys, so please be careful with them. Sofa bed will not be made up on your arrival unless specified in advance.
transit: You can take trains from Stockwell tube station [Norther Line - Black, and Victoria Line - Blue], or take one of the many well-connected bus routes serving the area, many of which run 24 hours. From Stockwell Station using the Northern Line, it will take just 10 minutes to be at London Bridge, 12 minutes to Bank, and 20 minutes to Kings Cross St Pancras. Using the Victoria Line, you can reach Oxford Circus in 15 minutes, or Victoria (for Buckingham Palace) in 10 minutes.
access: Guests will have access to the entire apartment.
interaction: Myself and my property management team will be available 24/7 via Airbnb, email, or phone to provide any assistance you may need.

neighborhood_overview: Tooting is a great area with a high street featuring near enough everything you could possibly need. There are supermarkets, ethnic markets, pubs, bars and some great, inexpensive restaurants, including South Asian, Lebanese, Italian, Spanish, Moroccan and the odd British. We're also not far from St George's hospital should anything unexpected occur!
notes: The house was built around a century ago, but rest assured, plenty of improvements have taken place since then. On a quiet and desirable street it offers easy access to the wide open spaces of Tooting Commons, local shops and a sub 10 minute walk to the underground stations.  For fitness enthusiasts, we have the athletics track, the famous Lido, tennis courts, football pitches and plenty of space to go running in the local vicinity.
transit: Local buses include the 319, the 249, the 219, the 155, the 355; taking you to Chelsea, Battersea, Clapham, Brixton and Elephant & Castle.  In under ten minutes you can walk to either Tooting Bec/Broadway stations on the Northern line of the Underground. One stop on is Balham station, which links to the overground train system taking you to Clapham Junction or Victoria. A 15 minute amble will take you to Tooting Rail station, where you can get into central London and beyond. Parking is available but permits are required Mon-Fri 9.30am - 4.30 pm.

name: Family home in Sydenham
summary: Our family home is in the vibrant and leafy neighbourhood of Sydenham. Experience life like a Londoner while only being 15 mins from central London by train/tube! The house can accommodate a maximum of 6 adults, 2 children (or small adults) and 1 infant.  We are a stone's throw from local shops, cafes and restaurants and the genuinely stunning Mayow Park (Green Flag Award 2015). Our house is a great place to base yourself for easy access into London. Come and see for yourself, you'll love it!
space: Spacious and light house with 2 double bedrooms and a single room with a small single bed and spare trundle bed underneath (which we would prefer to keep for the exclusive use of children but happy to discuss). The downstairs lounge also houses a king size sofa bed which can accommodate 2 adults who may find this more comfortable than the single beds upstairs. We have a large, private garden with trampoline with safety net and we're 5 mins walk away from the beautiful Mayow Park (Green Flag Award 2015). We have a number of cafes and restaurants nearby and Sydenham Rd houses a variety of local grocers and butchers who can cater for every taste.

neighborhood_overview: Sydenham is a vibrant creative community with a growing arts scene and festival. It has excellent local food and grocery shops and a number of lovely cafes and restaurants catering to all tastes. We have four parks nearby including Mayow Park and Crystal Palace Park and the Horniman Museum can be reached on foot within 25 mins or in 10 mins by bus. The road we live on is a quiet crescent overlooking St Michael's vicarage and church.
notes: We have a trampoline and numerous outdoor toys for children which we can make available upon request.  We also have a Weber BBQ which we are happy to make accessible to guests.
transit: We are a short walk to three mainline stations including: Sydenham (Zone 3) -15 mins to London Bridge, 25 mins to trendy Hoxton and Shoreditch, 35 minutes to Highbury & Islington, 40 mins to Gatwick Airport Lower Sydenham (Zone 4) -18 mins to Waterloo, 23 mins to Charing Cross Penge East (Zone 4) - 15 mins to London Victoria
access: The house is fully equipped with all amenities: WiFi, cable tv, Netflix etc.  The kitchen is fully equipped with crockery, cutlery, dishwasher, washer/dryer, microwave, Gaggia coffee machine. We are happy to arrange grocery deliveries and can stock the fridge with essentials if needed. We can provide some infant/childrens' equipment and toys for all ages upon request - just let us know what you need and we will let you know if we can  accommodate. There is a large decked area in the garden with dining table and chairs and a Weber kettle BBQ which guests are welcome to use. Guests will have access to all areas except the loft and garage. There is a secure driveway on the grounds of the house and free parking on the road outside.  While we try and "depersonalise" the space as much as possible, this is our primary residence so it will still feel homely and have a few signs of our family life dotted around.
interaction: We won't be present during your stay so will liaise with you re collection of keys, but we will always contactable.
house_rules: We ask our guests to kindly leave our house as you find it. And sorry but: No smoking inside  No shoes upstairs No late parties, stag or hen do's. No more than the maximum number of overnight guests. And please understand but we reserve the right to cancel if we don't feel that the guest has provided sufficient information to satisfy us that the rules will be observed.
host_about:
My husband and I love good food, water and snow sports and we try and visit places where we can satisfy at least one of those interests ;) 

When we travel we definitely prefer to experience a place like locals so Airbnb is usually our first port of call when we need to book accommodation. We like to get off the beaten track and discover places for ourselves instead of just ticking off the main tourist sights (though we do like to do that too). Our most recent travel destinations have been to Lisbon, Berlin and the Arcachon region of France.

At home, we love cooking for friends, camping and going to festivals. 

We hope you will enjoy staying in our home and that you feel comfortable and at ease. Please feel free to contact us if you have any questions about our place.

neighborhood_overview: Stoke Newington is an exceptional part of London. With a rich cultural history and a flourishing number of independent shops, cafes, restaurants and bars, you are never short of things to do. A short walk from the apartment you can find Stoke Newington Church street which has everything you could need - organic food shops, lovely pubs, independent shops, restaurants, beautiful architecture and Clissold Park. For a nightlife Dalston and Hackney are on your doorstep. Highbury and Islington, Angel and Finsbury Park also offer a host of great nights out. There is also a wonderful local wine and beer shop that offer everything you could need at the top of the road, a little bakery that is open 24 hours a day and 'The Best Turkish Kebab' in London. For parks near the apartment Hackney Downs, Clissold Park and Finsbury Park are all within walking distance. Other lovely and useful places we'd recommend include Sutton & Sons Fish and Chips, Franco Manca, Birthdays - a great club in Dalston, Sai

In terms of walking it is 5 mins to Stoke Newington Church Street, 5 mins to Rectory Road, 10 mins to Dalston Kingsland, 30 mins to Broadway Market and 30 walk to Highbury & Islington. Uber's are also available all the time.

neighborhood_overview: It’s impossible to think of Parsons Green without Sloane Rangers springing to mind. After all, it’s just down the road from Chelsea and a local pub, The White Horse, is known as the Sloaney Pony on account of the posh types that drink there. Many of the cast of Made In Chelsea have been spotted in the area at some point, and pinstripe shirts far outnumber baseball caps. Parsons Green is actually part of Fulham, rather than Chelsea, and lies between Fulham Road and New Kings Road. With great bars and restaurants, bijou stores and a Sunday farmers’ market, it manages to squeeze a lot into its relatively compact area. It has the ambience of a smart village in the heart of London. On a late Sunday morning, you’re just as likely to see families sipping lattes and baby-cinos outside cafes as you are to find Hooray Henrys trying to cure hangovers with Bloody Marys. Even the chains are upmarket – there’s a Little Waitrose, Space NK and Cote Brasserie, plus a healthy cluster of independents. Go
transit: There is a bus stop ( Route 22 ) just 2 mins walk away that takes you directly to Piccadilly Circus via Kings Road, Sloane Square & Knights bridge. Parsons Green Tube Station and Fulham Broadway Tube Station ( Both District Line towards Wimbledon) are 7-8 mins walk away.  Stamford Bridge ( for all the Chelsea fans or not!) is 10 mins walk away.

neighborhood_overview: Bloomsbury exudes high culture without pretenses. Known for its array of specialised institutions, Bloomsbury remains mild-mannered despite its cultural bragging rights. neighborhood_overview: It’s impossible to think of Parsons Green without Sloane Rangers springing to mind. After all, it’s just down the road from Chelsea and a local pub, The White Horse, is known as the Sloaney Pony on account of the posh types that drink there. Many of the cast of Made In Chelsea have been spotted in the area at some point, and pinstripe shirts far outnumber baseball caps. Parsons Green is actually part of Fulham, rather than Chelsea, and lies between Fulham Road and New Kings Road. With great bars and restaurants, bijou stores and a Sunday farmers’ market, it manages to squeeze a lot into its relatively compact area. It has the ambience of a smart village in the heart of London. On a late Sunday morning, you’re just as likely to see families sipping lattes and baby-cinos outside cafes as you are to find Hooray Henrys trying to cure hangovers with Bloody Marys. Even the chains are upmarket – there’s a Little Waitrose, Space NK and Cote Brasserie, plus a healthy cluster of independents. Go
transit: There is a bus stop ( Route 22 ) just 2 mins walk away that takes you directly to Piccadilly Circus via Kings Road, Sloane Square & Knights bridge. Parsons Green Tube Station and Fulham Broadway Tube Station ( Both District Line towards Wimbledon) are 7-8 mins walk away. Stamford Bridge ( for all the Chelsea fans or not!) is 10 mins walk away.

summary: Big, bright, beautiful double room in a funkily restored victorian house, oozing with charm, located in one of the nicest streets in the whole of Brixton - the hippest place to live, and go out in London.
space: This lovely double room has big sash windows, high ceilings, and sky lights - in summer it's just amazing to be in. There's a big comfortable iron bed with a new mattress, a victorian chest of drawers and large double wardrobe with full length mirrors. Bedsheets and towels are provided.  On the first floor you'll find a fabulous funky bathroom with a roll top bath that takes two and a walk in rain shower. There's also a hidden washer/dryer.  The downstairs has a lovely double lounge, diner and kitchen with programmable HUE lighting, funky features everywhere, a piano, coloured light strips in the floor and walls. And french doors open onto a peaceful private garden. There's sky and tivo for movie lovers, and an amazing 1970s bright red leather sofa for lounging in.

And french doors open onto a peaceful private garden. There's sky and tivo for movie lovers, and an amazing 1970s bright red leather sofa for lounging in. Guests can use the
neighborhood_overview: The house is located on one of the most beautiful streets in Brixton.  With a fabulous local pub - The Elm Park Tavern 50 meters away, just down our street - where there's also a convenience store. Just a minute's walk down Brixton Hill and you'll land at The White Horse - pretty much the best place to enjoy a Friday or Saturday night in London - and it's free to get in. There are tons of other brilliant nightspots within a stone's throw - but we hardly ever go anywhere else - and you can dance until 4am. For those with energy, there's plenty to do after that of course, with clubs and house parties going well into the next day.  Brixton is the best place to live in London. It's got a massively exciting vibe, beautiful living spaces, amazing restaurants and the coolest clubs and bars - all within walking distance.  You can get to central london in less than 10 mins for sightseeing - or access anywhere at all from the amazing underground network. But at night, you can go out, meet amazin
transit: Brixton Underground is just a couple of minutes down the hill.  Brixton village is a minutes walk from there. From the underground you can get to Victoria in 7 minutes, London Bridge in 8, Oxford Circus in 10, Kings Cross/Euston/St Pancras in 12 or Paddington in 19.  Tubes and busses come literally every minute now. And you can use any debit card if you have a CONNECT sign. Or buy an oyster card from the local shop.  There's a bus stop 30 seconds from the house, and more than 40 pass every hour. All will take you into different parts of London, or ferry you to the centre of Brixton, at the underground, in seconds (which is fastest for heading into central London ). Once you've taken a few (tubes or busses) the rest are free - if you stay within Zones 1 and 2.  On foot, Brockwell park is 3 minutes walk. And it's a lovely walk across it to get to Herne Hill or Dulwich in 10-15, two lovely quiet neighbourhoods where there are more nice places to eat and drink. You can also walk to Clapham
access: Guests can use the whole house and garden and any of the facilities - including the washer/dryer, and entertainment system.  The 1st floor bathroom is shared with my best friend Courage, who's very friendly, and has a bedroom on a separate floor.  The downstairs lounge, diner, kitchen and private garden are all for use with whoever is staying.  in the kitchen, you can use all utensils and kitchen supplies, and we can give you a food cupboard if you want to stay a while:)
interaction: Courage lives in and looks after the house. He's  very easy going, and will be happy to show you the cool places to go in Brixton. Any questions/recommendations about the house, area, transport etc in advance, I can help you with by phone or email. I'm living in Denmark at the moment so on a similar time zone.
house_rules: Please remember that you're sharing the house with the person whose home it is; so please treat it as you would your own home.
host_about:
I'm a film maker by trade but now run a non profit in Nepal.  Recently I got married there to Line - a Dane - in an entirely crazy Hindu ceremony with a thousand guests. We won't try that again. Now we have a baby and a lovely apartment in Aarhus, Denmark:)   

Our house in Brixton (London) is a very special place. I bought it as a ruin, 15 years ago, and spent 8 years rebuilding it. I took the roof off, all the floors up and every wall except the two party walls down to the ground. I had lots of fun with it, cutting holes and letting light into unexpected places and and it's now a space that makes me smile whenever I'm in it. I hope it will make you smile also.

neighborhood_overview: Our street is wonderfully quiet and picturesque, in the heart of Hackney Downs. Located in vibrant Hackney, with an excellent arts and music scene, there's tonnes to do here. There's great food, nice places to drink cocktails or a local ale, vintage shops galore, food markets, places to party all night, or the canal for a walk with the kids. You certainly won't be short of things to do in Hackney! Many of our favourite London spots are extremely close by. London Fields with its Broadway Market is a short walk away, the canal offers a wonderful walk through the East side of London and offers an abundance of breweries and restaurants to break up your walk. Columbia Road Flower on a Sunday is a must see and only a short bus journey away, as is all the great nightlife on offer in Shoreditch and Hoxton. There is no better place than Hackney.
transit: Hackney Downs overground station is a 6 minute walk away and Hackney Central is an 8 minute walk away. Both have direct trains to Liverpool St, London Fields (1 stop), Angel, the Olympic Park and many other destinations. It will take the following time to get to the major tourist destinations on public transport: West End (Oxford St) - 40 minutes  The City (Liverpool St) - 18 minutes Notting Hill - 45 minutes Olympic Park - 20 minute (walk) Columbia Road flower market - 30 minute (walk) There is also an abundance of bus routes that service the area too! If you have any queries we can tell you the easiest or the most scenic ways to get from A to B.

Walking distance to the American School in London and London Business School. Edwardian era mansions and tree-lined streets comprise Maida Vale, a predominately residential neighbourhood in west London. Floating homes also characterise the area—houseboats and gondolas drift through this “Little Venice” thanks to the convergence of canals near its southern border. Peppered with local bars and cafes, this reserved neighbourhood is better for swirling cocktails than swigging beers after (or before) a commute to central London. The journey is easy enough—Maida Vale has its own tube station.

name: Beautifully renovated Victorian flat in Camberwell
summary: Come stay in one of two lovely first-floor double bedrooms available in my three-bed apartment located on a beautiful, quiet road of Victorian terraces, next to Burgess Park and just down the road from vibrant, hipster Peckham & foodie Camberwell Green.  Just renovated to a luxurious level (underfloor heating, high-speed internet to all rooms, NEST thermostat, new carpets, designer Italian kitchen, new bathrooms, new windows, juliet balcony, soundproofing, new paint)! You will fall in love!
space: The room is lovely and was recently refurbished and painted a beautiful shade of white, with lovely dark detailing on the woodwork and newly made double glazed timber sash windows. This is not your average rental, but rather a home, and a labour of love. Having recently refurbished over the last 6 months, I have chosen and designed every detail of the interior. That means a very high level of finish, but also attention to how it all works - heated mirrors in the bathrooms, high-speed internet ports in all rooms, luxury Samsung oven, fully integrated designer Italian made kitchen, and induction hobs, and fully smart lighting (every room has multiple dimmers, all controllable via iphone or intelligent wall switches).

neighborhood_overview: On one side we have Camberwell, which is incredibly for foodies with a cornucopia of great restaurants & welcoming pubs and friendly locals. On the other we have Peckham, which is one of the best night spots in town.
notes: Please note I have some lovely builders putting the finishing touches to the flat below. They are on the painting stage, so shouldn't make too much noise, but will be active normally from 9-6 for the next two weeks (scheduled to finish mid-October)
transit: If you're lucky enough / crazy enough to be travelling by car in London, you can park it in the road for free. Otherwise bikes and feet are the best way to navigate the local area, with 15-minute buses to take you to the nearest travel terminus (Elephant & Castle) if you're venturing into the centre of town to explore everything the city has to offer. Uber cabs are also a really great and pretty inexpensive option if buses aren't for you.
access: Please just make yourself at home. Feel free to use the laundry facilities, the bath, the lounge and the lovely designer Italian kitchen.
interaction: I've lived in London for nearly ten years now, so can claim to be an adopted Londoner! If you want insider tips on getting about town, what to see that's not on the tourist trail, where the locals go to drink, and where to get the best burgers or fish and chips, just let me know. I love sharing this local knowledge and meeting folk from around the world - and this is one of the reasons I'm so keen to Airbnb my spare rooms. I am out at work during the days, as an advertising exec, and am often out in the evenings, but when I'm around you'll find the atmosphere really warm and friendly.
house_rules: You're absolutely free to smoke in the garden, but please not in the room, the next guest probably won't thank you. Please save those Tina Turner renditions for London's karaoke bars, but otherwise feel free to treat the place as your home away from home.
host_about:
Hi there I am a recovering ad man, turned social entrepreneur, and freelance documentary photographer. I am very laid back, sociable and easy to get to know. I love to laugh with old friends and make new ones. I love live music, good food, design, art and travel. I love to explore the city and travel the world whenever I can. I am also passionate about learning languages and have picked up French, Spanish and Mandarin Chinese along the way. 

On my wide-ranging travels I have stayed at a lot of hostels and home stays and have always been able to muck in, make new friends and enjoy the vibe. I also have a regular stream of international friends coming to use my place as a base. As a host I look forward to giving something back to the international community.

5 things I can't live without? Music. Books. Laughter. My camera. Oh, and great food!

summary: Step out of this tranquil, garden flat in Balham,  and in 5 minutes you're at the tube (subway)/train station,  with easy access to the vibrant culture  of London. Great local supermarkets, organic foods, boutique shops, parks and bohemian cafes.
space: Hi, if you're looking for somewhere that's got a bit of character, period style  and is comfortable, cosy and clean, then you may like my home. Built In 1905, with wooden floor boards and original Edwardian fireplaces, your room has a single futon chair-bed, chest of drawers and small mirror with shared access to the owner's kitchen, bathroom, living area and patio.  My place would suit you if you're an  independent and easy going woman  who is just looking for a base  when visiting London on holiday, study trips or short term work assignments.  There are a number of coffee bars and a local library nearby, all  with WiFi access if you need to do some work, as the room is not set up with a desk.  If you want to know  a bit more about the flat, location and proximity to any places, for example,  hospitals, the City or universities, just drop me a line.

neighborhood_overview: Balham is pretty  relaxed, some say bohemian!  It has great supermarkets  including Sainsbury's, Waitrose and Lidls, which are open from 7am - 11pm (except Sundays), a large organic store, lots of upcoming trendy breakfast cafes, quirky boutique shops, a daily local fruit and veg market, and lots of great low-average priced restaurants catering for a wide range of tastes - Italian, French, Thai, Indian, Sri Lankan, Vietnamese,  Nepalese,  Lebanese, Middle Eastern,  and modern British, as well as fast food places, including fish & chips, kebabs, McDonalds and Nandos and home delivery services; A bus stop away is Tooting with some of the best South Indian food places  in London, or head to Brixton for some authentic  Caribbean food, including jerk chicken, curry goat or rice and peas!  Balham has some good pubs, including The Bedford which hosts the famous comedy club - The Banana Caberet, and live folk/blues  music; for film lovers, we're   within 10 minutes of local cinemas at Clapham
notes: THIS LISTING IS FOR FEMALE GUESTS ONLY. I was unable to respond to the comments posted by a long stay guest in Dec 2015 as I was on holiday . To reassure you,  please see the comments by  other reviewers and judge  whether this single negative review reflects more on the guest's personality  or the host. Please feel free to contact me if you have any queries linked to any reviewer's comments.
transit: The flat is very convenient to public transport , and is 20 - 30  minutes door-door to Waterloo and the South Bank, Oxford Street, and the National museums,  art galleries and theatres.  Local minicab services are plenty or London Black cabs are parked at the local train station. There is a good Zipcar car rental service in the area.  For day trips, Balham,  "the gateway to the South,"  is within easy access to the trendy seaside resort of  Brighton, and the  historic sights of  Portsmouth and Winchester.  Direct trains stop at Victoria, and it's easy to get to Gatwick, Heathrow and Luton airports,  and St Pancras Eurostar - just drop me a line and I'll send you directions on booking. If you have a car/motorbike, there is metered street parking and you can get 1-day  parking permits from the local Balham library.
access: Clean linen, allergy mattress protector and towels will be provided. Please help yourself to tea, coffee and sugar.  For breakfast,  there are plenty of good breakfast/brunch cafes, coffee shops and restaurants within 5 minutes of the flat.  The kitchen is available for microwave meals only but food/fridge or freezer storage is no longer provided after a poor experience with a long stay guest in December 2015. The electricity sockets are 3 square pin  but a travel adaptor  is available.  Guidebooks about London, including London walks and information about cultural events at our museums, art galleries and theatres   are readily available in the flat. This is a residential house and all common areas are shared with myself; you are welcome to use the patio garden and TV/ DVD/ipod player. The flat has gas central heating in all rooms except the kitchen.
interaction: I enjoy having people over to stay and making guests feel welcomed,  relaxed and comfortable.  During the day, I'm pretty busy and I often work from home. I'm more than happy to chat and offer any help, but I'll generally  leave you to get on with your stuff unless you wish otherwise.
house_rules: No smoking indoors, but no problem if you wish to smoke occasionally  in the back garden. This is a residential home so please  be mindful of energy wastage and just turn off  lights when you are not using, and come in quietly if you're out late. That said, you're  free to come and go as you wish.  No additional guests without prior consent. Not really rules, but I'd really appreciate if you would treat the flat with respect  and keep everything clean, tidy and as you found it  - many thanks.
host_about:
Relaxed  and easy going.

Hi, I was born in London, grew up in the Caribbean  and have lived in Balham for many years. I work with children, families and schools, enjoy the arts and current affairs, and am happy to give you any information that you need as a visitor to London/England.  Although the flat is shared, you'll have your privacy.

space: The room is lovely and was recently refurbished and painted a beautiful shade of white, with lovely dark detailing on the woodwork and newly made double glazed timber sash windows. That means a very high level of finish, but also attention to how it all works - heated mirrors in the bathrooms, high-speed internet ports in all rooms, luxury Samsung oven, fully integrated designer Italian made kitchen, and induction hobs, and fully smart lighting (every room has multiple dimmers, all controllable via iphone or intelligent wall switches).

notes: Please note I have some lovely builders putting the finishing touches to the flat below. They are on the painting stage, so shouldn't make too much noise, but will be active normally from 9-6 for the next two weeks (scheduled to finish mid-October)
transit: If you're lucky enough / crazy enough to be travelling by car in London, you can park it in the road for free. Otherwise bikes and feet are the best way to navigate the local area, with 15-minute buses to take you to the nearest travel terminus (Elephant & Castle) if you're venturing into the centre of town to explore everything the city has to offer. Uber cabs are also a really great and pretty inexpensive option if buses aren't for you.
access: Please just make yourself at home. Feel free to use the laundry facilities, the bath, the lounge and the lovely designer Italian kitchen.
interaction: I've lived in London for nearly ten years now, so can claim to be an adopted Londoner! If you want insider tips on getting about town, what to see that's not on the tourist trail, where the locals go to drink, and where to get the best burgers or fish and chips, just let me know. I love sharing this local knowledge and meeting folk from around the world - and this is one of the reasons I'm so keen to Airbnb my spare rooms. I am out at work during the days, as an advertising exec, and am often out in the evenings, but when I'm around you'll find the atmosphere really warm and friendly.
house_rules: You're absolutely free to smoke in the garden, but please not in the room, the next guest probably won't thank you. Please save those Tina Turner renditions for London's karaoke bars, but otherwise feel free to treat the place as your home away from home.
host_about:
Hi there I am a recovering ad man, turned social entrepreneur, and freelance documentary photographer. I am very laid back, sociable and easy to get to know. I love to laugh with old friends and make new ones. I love live music, good food, design, art and travel. I love to explore the city and travel the world whenever I can. I am also passionate about learning languages and have picked up French, Spanish and Mandarin Chinese along the way. 

On my wide-ranging travels I have stayed at a lot of hostels and home stays and have always been able to muck in, make new friends and enjoy the vibe. I also have a regular stream of international friends coming to use my place as a base. As a host I look forward to giving something back to the international community.

5 things I can't live without? Music. Books. Laughter. My camera. Oh, and great food!

summary: Comfy room in Victoria Park, East London. Very close to Shoreditch, Broadway Market, Columbia Road, Brick Lane and the Olympic Park. Bethnal Green’s station is just 10 mins away, while many bus stops are just a short walk from the house.
space: The 70 sqft room offers a very comfortable bed with fresh sheets, duvet, towels, hair dryer, hanging clothes rack, shelves, mirror, bedside table and fibre wifi. There’s both a bathroom and a toilet that you will be sharing with a couple only. The apartment is situated in a maisonette house: it’s on two floors and very spacious. On the ground floor there’s an open plan kitchen and living room with high ceilings and wooden floor, while in the first floor there are two bedrooms and a bathroom. There’s also another toilet in the ground floor with wc and sink only. Throughout the apartment there are both regular and skylight windows, which make the house very bright during day time.

Your room is just two steps from the bathroom that offers a combined bath
neighborhood_overview: Our apartment is situated just off Roman Road, right in the middle of Victoria Park, Bethnal Green, Hackney Wick and Bow. The nice and historical Roman Road market takes place three times a week just right outside our house. Brick Lane, Shoreditch, Columbia Road & Broadway Market - with a huge mix of galleries, shops, markets, bars, pubs and restaurants - are all very close to our place. You can also find many interesting local attractions in the neighbourhood including Lauriston Road Village - for its beautiful cafes, pubs and stores - and Columbia Road, Broadway Market and Dalston for their markets, restaurants and nightlife.
notes: Check in: 12 noon  Check out: 10 am More often than not we can be flexible, so please let us know if you would like to check out later, or leave your bags during your last day.
transit: There are many buses and trains that you can use: Bethnal Green’s central line - which is one of the main and fastest line in London - is just 10 mins away, as well as Mile End and Bow stations, where you can also take the District, Hammersmith & City line and DLR. Buses and night buses to central London are frequent and only a 1 minute walk from the house. Examples of journey times from Bethnal Green station:  Oxford Circus = 20 mins by tube Liverpool Street = 3 mins by tube / 11 mins by bus / 25 mins walking Shoreditch High Street = 10 minutes by bus / 20 mins walking  Airports:  London City Airport - 15 mins by car Stanstead - 35 mins by car  Heathrow - 60 mins by car  Gatwick - 60 mins by car Driving: If you are driving we can arrange parking access for your car but please let us know well in advance.
access: Your room is just two steps from the bathroom that offers a combined bath and shower. Guests have use of hair, body and bath products. The kitchen if fully equipped and you are welcome to use it for some light cooking. There is a fibre fast connection throughout the house that you can enjoy. We’ve also got a NETFLIX and BT Sport account that you’re welcome to use. You also have the use of an iron, ironing board and washing machine.
interaction: When you arrive you will be greeted, shown around and given a set of keys for your stay. I’m home most days and my partner most evenings. We spend our weekends walking around this lovely area, enjoying Victoria Park and the many nice restaurants and coffee places in East London. If you should need anything or have any questions before, during or after your stay we are always on hand. We love meeting new people and look forward to welcoming you into our home!
house_rules: No smoking inside the apartment. No music after 10pm. Please clean up after yourself and leave the place as you found it.

neighborhood_overview: Hanger Lane is a major road in the Ealing area of London. It forms the westernmost part of the A406 North Circular as it runs north from Gunnersbury Avenue as it crosses the A4020 Uxbridge Road at Ealing Common to meet the A40 Western Avenue at the Hanger Lane Gyratory System. This complex and busy junction incorporates the Hanger Lane tube station on the London Underground. There is a short stretch of Hanger Lane north of the Gyratory System which is not part of the North Circular, becoming the A4005 to Alperton.

neighborhood_overview: Stockwell probably got the second half of its name from a local well; the other half is from "stoc", which was Old English for a tree trunk or post. From the thirteenth to the start of the nineteenth century, Stockwell was a rural manor at the edge of London. Today a cosmopolitan mix of inhabitants, professionals, poets, musicians, artists, activists, anarchists and bohemians live in the area.    Restaurants and bars, many of which are Portuguese due to Stockwell being home to a large Portuguese community.
notes: The great British weather never fails to annoy so bring a rain mac and umbrella just in case.

Zone 2 Stockwell tube station is 3 mins walking and is on the Victoria and Northern Line.  Bus number 2 goes to the West End/ Mayfair & Marylebone then back to Brixton  Bus 88 from Clapham to Trafalgar square / piccadily/ Whitehall / Camden which is a great value alternative day out.
